HEADWORD: Digenea
<hw>Di*ge"ne*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ race,
offspring.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Trematoda in
which alternate generations occur, the immediate young not resembling
their parents.</def>⟦br⟧
